Why I Built This

Back to README: ./README.md

My cloud storage limits were growing, and instead of increasing monthly subscriptions, I decided to build a self-hosted stack on hardware I already had.

What this project helped me learn:

- Linux server administration
- Dockerized operations
- DNS and domain routing
- SSL/TLS fundamentals
- Monitoring and incident response
- Backup and recovery planning

The result is a practical personal homelab that is useful day-to-day and also acts as a long-term learning platform.
